Both output files have been written. Summary of findings:

The analysis surfaced a single, very clean treatment-effect subgroup driving essentially all signal in the dataset for `objective_response`:

**Active treatment subgroup: feature_014=1 AND feature_001=1 AND feature_021=1 AND feature_026=0 AND feature_009=0**
- n=1,790 (3.6% of cohort), response rate 78.6%
- All other 96.4% of patients: response rate 16.5% (essentially constant background, regardless of which subset of the three positive features they have)
- OR ≈ 18.6, risk difference ≈ 62 percentage points, p << 1e-300

Key structure:
- **Multiplicative (3-way) synergy**: feature_014, feature_001, feature_021 each have ~null effect alone — the benefit appears only when all three are co-present (3-way interaction β=+2.13, p=2.5e-92).
- **Two parallel suppressors**: feature_026 and feature_009 each completely abolish the triple-positive effect when positive (interaction p=2e-62 and p=4e-42 respectively); neither has any prognostic effect outside the treatment context. Having both is no worse than having one — parallel/redundant suppression.
- Other features (feature_004, feature_020, feature_024, etc.) act as general additive prognostic factors and modulate but do not abolish the treatment effect.

Files written:
- `transcript.json` — 10 iterations, validated against `transcript_schema.json`
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative walk-through and consolidated subgroup hypothesis
